# Workflow Pattern

Authoritative: `docs/30-Implementation/agent-workflow-pattern.md`. Every beat
follows its loop: small Linear beat, confirm understanding, plan, implement,
reflect in vault, alignment check, draft PR, review, merge green.

Design system only — tokens in `apps/web/src/styles/app.css`, `cn()` from
`apps/web/src/lib/utils.ts`, theme in `apps/web/src/theme/*`, atoms/composites
in `apps/web/src/components/`. No agent-invented style/layout, no raw hex, no
arbitrary Tailwind values, no inline visual `style=`.

Ask, don't work around. Unclear architecture/feature, missing ADR, or missing
design primitive is a stop condition: open a Linear issue tagged for Nico, mark
the beat Blocked, halt — never guess, stub, or shortcut. Reuses the escalation
path in `.cursor/rules/99-safety.mdc`.

Vault is living documentation. Code and its vault delta ship in the same PR. A
change contradicting a documented ADR/architecture decision is escalated, not
merged. Keep every decision modular and future-proof; one-way doors need an
ADR + Nico sign-off.
